parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Issues - Pulling to the Right
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle's tendency to pull to the right while driving on flat straight roads can cause the driver to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or tight
the vehicle pulls to the right
the steering wheel requires resistance to keep the vehicle on the road
the lane keep safety feature must be turned off to avoid jerking back
the pull issue becomes more noticeable after taking right turns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stiff steering wheel and wandering of the vehicle can cause the driver to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff
the vehicle wanders or steers away automatically
the issue is more pronounced at higher speeds (above 45 mph)
the issue persists even with lane-assist features turned off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the anti-theft system can lead to theft and damage to the vehicle, including the steering column.
symptoms: The anti-theft system fails to protect the vehicle
resulting in break-ins and damage to the steering column and windows.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unidentified steering issue can cause the driver to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: An abnormal clunking sound comes from underneath the vehicle while making left turns
no warning lights are illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unrepaired Recall - Front Lower Control Arm
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unrepaired recall can cause the driver to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The front lower control arm is recalled but not repaired
despite multiple visits to the dealership.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to become stuck in gear, unable to move, or experience sudden loss of power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle will not move or reverse
the transmission slips or hesitates
the transmission whines or makes unusual noises
the transmission fails to engage gears
the vehicle experiences sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The use of refurbished or used transmissions with used parts can lead to premature failure, causing the vehicle to become stuck in gear, unable to move, or experience sudden loss of power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails repeatedly
the transmission fails shortly after replacement
the vehicle experiences sudden loss of power
the transmission slips or hesitates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of oil in the coolant can cause engine damage, overheating, and potentially lead to engine failure, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Oil is present in the coolant
the engine overheats
the vehicle experiences loss of power
the engine fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lane keep assist system can cause the vehicle to unexpectedly merge into another lane, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle unexpectedly merges into another lane
the lane keep assist feature fails to alert the driver
the vehicle slams on the brakes without warning
the wheel tries to jerk the vehicle into another lane
the system malfunctions in specific areas or randomly.
